# Workflow migration

This file applies only when adopting dstack into a repository that used the original Markdown task workflow.

Install all dstack skills and run:

```text
/migrate-workflow
```

The migration skill scans `docs/src/planned-features.md`, feature `design.md` files, and legacy `tasks.md` files; assigns stable feature numbers; imports executable work into Beads; preserves the existing documentation hierarchy; and archives legacy task files after reconciliation.

Run the migration on a clean branch or worktree and review each mechanical and semantic commit boundary.
